    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "433a9e99_12c44bb9",
        "filename": "util/stream/log_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-10T19:09:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This value is duplicated in tests, documented in the header, and is relevant knowledge for a user of this class. I think it makes sense to upgrade it to a public static class member OR pass it through the constructor so the caller can decide how large a log message to tolerate.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "4e14bcd3d779f04872d9015bc44ae18e7081a946",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "43979fee_e9d2429d",
        "filename": "util/stream/log_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000825
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-10T23:45:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From previous review (https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/crashpad/crashpad/+/1745355/5/util/stream/zlib_output_stream.h#46), IIUC, Mark preferred to simple the implementation by not sharing these const with test, I think that is fine as it is implementation detail and shouldn\u0027t be changed often, and once changed, the test should be modified as well.\n\nIf passed through constructor, it isn\u0027t implementation detail, and kLineBufferSize might also be passed in.\n\nI tend to keep it as implementation detail, what do you prefer to?",
      "parentUuid": "433a9e99_12c44bb9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "4e14bcd3d779f04872d9015bc44ae18e7081a946",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "266e454e_e5fb85fb",
        "filename": "util/stream/log_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-11T20:02:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree this is unlikely to change (and has limited enough scope that it would be easy to change if we need to) so take this comment as a nit and feel free to use your own judgement here. I\u0027m mostly intending to share my own thoughts on interface design.\n\nThe buffer in that review is an implementation detail because you can change it without any caller-visible effect. You can change the size of that buffer and expect that all your tests and other uses of the class continue to operate the same way they did before. It\u0027s only relevant to tests for testing edge cases.\n\nThese values *do* have a caller-visible effect. If kOutputCap is made too small, calls to Write() or Flush() will start failing and in that sense, the limit of how much the caller is allowed to write is public information.",
      "parentUuid": "43979fee_e9d2429d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "4e14bcd3d779f04872d9015bc44ae18e7081a946",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "033a3ddb_2f2bfb49",
        "filename": "util/stream/log_output_stream.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-10T19:09:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There\u0027s a comment in the NDK 20\u0027s header \u003candroid/log.h\u003e:\n\n * Log message text may be truncated to less than an implementation-specific\n * limit (1023 bytes).\n\nIs that referring to the same buffer?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 36,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "4e14bcd3d779f04872d9015bc44ae18e7081a946",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
